    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-19T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-19T04:00:00-05:00" n="785"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d785">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">660p.6131/89: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_SLA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-19T12:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 19, 1939—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received October 19—5:25
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>771. The press reports the signature today<note n="56" xml:id="d785fn56"
                        >Signature apparently took place on October 18, 1939.</note> of an agreement
                    between the Soviet Union and Latvia under the terms of which the total turnover
                    between the two countries will reach 60,000,000 lats, or three times the present
                    amount. Latvia is granted transit rights over Soviet railways and through the
                    ports of Murmansk, Soroka and <pb facs="1077" n="971" xml:id="pg_971"/> the
                    Black Sea, and in return grants to the Soviet Union “a wide extension of transit
                    facilities for Soviet goods through Latvian ports.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
